<subSubSection id="D8FB6574FFFABD501F9CA9AE91FC004B" pageId="5" pageNumber="466" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="905E36FFFFFABD501F9CA9AE91FC004B" blockId="5.[178,1085,218,299]" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">
Comparative notes: This species is distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="57E14D7CFFFABD501CCEA9AF90DE006E" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Orsunius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="A295EAEDFFFABD501CCEA9AF94180190" box="[992,1085,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="466">Orsunius</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="F4704B0EFFFABD501E1DA98C919E006E" author="ASSING V" box="[307,443,248,270]" journalOrPublisher="Linzer Biologische Beitrage" pageId="5" pageNumber="466" pagination="221 - 244" part="43" refId="ref8323" refString="ASSING V. (2011): Orsunius gen. nov. from the Oriental region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae: Medonina). - Linzer Biologische Beitrage 43 (1): 221 - 244." title="Orsunius gen. nov. from the Oriental region (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae: Medonina)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING 2011</bibRefCitation>
) particularly by the shape of the male sternite VIII and by the morphology of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
